comments.body:
The file is missing an {{=}} character between the option's name and its value.  If the value wasn't a URL you would have seen an error, but python allows one to use {{:}} in place of {{=}}, making that line function as if it was this one:
{code}
monitoring-url https = //cloudwatch.hp-aw2-1.hpcloudsvc.com/services/CloudWatch
{code}

I can't fix that without re-implementing part of the python standard library or losing euca2ools.ini's forward-compatibility.  :-(
